# Lint before commit

Before any `git commit` in this repo:

1. Run `pnpm lint` (`biome check .`).
2. If it fails, run `pnpm format` (`biome check --write .`) and fix any remaining **errors** (warnings alone are OK if `pnpm lint` exits 0).
3. Re-run `pnpm lint` and confirm exit code 0.
4. Only then stage the lint/format fixes (if any) and commit.

Do not commit when `pnpm lint` is red. CI runs `pnpm lint` on every push to `main`.

Optional local enforcement (once per clone):

```bash
git config core.hooksPath .githooks
```

That runs `pnpm lint` on every commit via [`.githooks/pre-commit`](.githooks/pre-commit).
